overview: The user started by asking for help cleaning up their Vercel
  dashboard, which had five projects for a single app. I identified and deleted
  four duplicate projects using the Vercel CLI, leaving only the main
  sleep-questionnaire project. Following this, the user requested assistance in
  setting up a development environment. I created a develop branch, pushed it to
  the repository, and guided the user on configuring branch-specific domains and
  environment variables in Vercel. A key adjustment was made to ensure
  NEXT_PUBLIC_SHOW_DEV_TOOLS was correctly scoped to only the preview
  environment, which involved removing it from production and redeploying.
  Finally, I deployed the develop branch and provided the user with the stable
  preview URL for their new development environment.
